---
import SiteLayout from "../../theme/layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import Badge from "../../theme/components/Badge.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Designing with tonal depth"
  description="A sample article page for the NocturnalZone Astro theme."
  type="article"
>
  <article class="nz-container nz-container--narrow">
    <p class="nz-eyebrow">May 1, 2026</p>
    <h1 class="nz-page-title">Designing with tonal depth.</h1>
    <div class="nz-actions">
      <Badge variant="accent">Design</Badge>
      <Badge>Astro</Badge>
    </div>

    <div class="nz-prose nz-section">
      <p>
        NocturnalZone uses tonal changes instead of heavy outlines. A surface should feel like a shift in light,
        not a box drawn around content.
      </p>
      <h2>Surfaces</h2>
      <p>
        Cards and panels use <code>--nz-bg-secondary</code> and move toward <code>--nz-bg-tertiary</code> on hover.
        This keeps the interface quiet while still providing interaction feedback.
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        The theme avoids hard page-section borders. Spacing and background tone carry the structure.
      </blockquote>
      <h2>Typography</h2>
      <p>
        Large headings do the expressive work. Body text stays readable, secondary, and calm.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
